<function>

access:  static public

name: fileExists

param: string, $file

return: bool

</function>

Hack for [[php file_exists()]] that checks the include_path.

* Parameters:

 * string //$file//: Check for this file in the include_path.

* Returns bool: True if the file exists and is readble in the include_path, false if not.

Hack for [[php file_exists()]] that checks the include_path.

Use this to see if a file exists anywhere in the include_path.

<code type="php">
$file = 'path/to/file.php';
if (Solar::fileExists('path/to/file.php')) {
    include $file;
}
</code>